File: In the CCTV video, the woman is being pulled and dragged by officers at a petrol station in Lyttleton, Pretoria. JOHANNESBURG - Tshwane Metro Police says it's investigating an incident involving a woman "manhandled" by metro police officers at a petrol station in Lyttleton, Pretoria. CCTV footage showing the woman being pulled and dragged by officers at the petrol station has gone viral. The woman allegedly failed to stop when flagged by the officers.  According to reports, the woman says she was scared and drove to the nearby petrol station. WATCH: JMPD investigating viral blood test video Police say investigations are at an advanced stage.